title: Fileless PowerShell Execution via Registry Base64 Payload
id: 9f3b1a42-6c4f-4a61-9f0d-2c7c4e7b1e91
status: experimental
description: >
  Detects PowerShell executing a Base64-encoded payload retrieved from
  the Windows Registry and executed via Invoke-Expression (IEX),
  a common fileless malware technique observed in T1059.001.
references:
  - https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1059/001/
  - https://github.com/redcanaryco/atomic-red-team
author: Busra Ugur
date: 2026/01/26
logsource:
  product: windows
  category: process_creation
detection:
  selection:
    Image|endswith: '\powershell.exe'
    CommandLine|contains|all:
      - 'FromBase64String'
      - 'Invoke-Expression'
      - 'Get-ItemProperty'
      - 'HKCU:\Software\'
  condition: selection
falsepositives:
  - Legitimate administrative scripts storing encoded data in registry
  - Red team simulations or atomic testing
level: medium
tags:
  - attack.execution
  - attack.t1059.001
  - attack.defense_evasion
